warnings.name: Discontinuity in base period
warnings.title: DISCONTINUITY
warnings.body: The procedure could not be completed because the relationship between the predicting and test variables in the most recent base year is significantly different from the relationship in earlier base years. This is commonly caused by a change in business conditions. Inspecting the scatter plot and plot of residuals for patterns and outlier clusters may help identify the cause. However, the model cannot be used for audit purposes. Next Steps: |Consider if events have occurred in the previous years that changed the relationship between the predicting and test variables. |Consider adjusting an existing predicting variable or introducing a new predicting variable to account for the change in the relationship. |Consider eliminating the earliest year(s) (assuming there are several years in the base). |For more information see examples provided in the Performing Substantive Analytical Procedures Guide section x.x. |To discuss further alternatives please submit an online support request online support request.
